dc_title_s: Poland 1:100,000. Brazesc Nad Bugiem, sheet P-18. A.M.S. M651 (G.S.G.S. 4416)
dc_description_s: AMS 2. Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section. G.S.G.S. 4416. Alternate title: Brazesc Nad Bugiem, Poland. Polyconic projection. Russian belt 4 grid. Relief shown by 10 meter contour intervals and spot elevations. With a glossary. Compiled from Poland, 1:100,000, Military Geographic Institute, sheets 40-37, 40-38, 41-37 and 41-38, 1942. Road classification based on British intelligence reports, 1943. Map states location as Poland though the map actually depicts Belarus.
dc_publisher_s: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, U.S. Army, 1945.
